HEADWORD: Hydrochloride
<hw>Hy`dro*chlo"ride</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound of hydrochloric acid with a base; -- distinguished from
a <xex>chloride</xex>, where only chlorine unites with the
base.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrocorallia</ent>⟦br⟧
